// 7.605 — 🟢 Online-discount 15% → 20% sweep across customer-facing copy. Source: Kat-feedback round 13 (`Green Life/KAT_FEEDBACK_2026_05_08.md`: "We are good to go on starting the 20% off online orders"). Closes the 2026-05-05 deferral. Sister of inv v279.405 (which flipped 5 staff-facing sites). 10 customer-facing files updated: app/page.tsx (12 sites: hero kicker, stat tile, badge, savings strip, CTA buttons, three-step flow, perks list, footer CTA, etc.) + app/llms.txt + app/llms-full.txt + app/faq (4 sites: appointments, redeem-loyalty, online-pickup, deals-Q) + app/brands/[slug] + app/sign-up/[[...sign-up]] (sign-up incentive) + app/heroes (FAQ "online already saves") + app/about (CTA) + app/blog/[slug] (CTA) + lib/store.ts (perks list). DB-side seed already shipped at 20% (inv migration 0059 'seed-online-orders-20'); this synchronizes the customer-facing surfaces. CSS gradient-position 15%-style references (radial-gradient circle at 15% 90%) intentionally untouched (CSS coords, not online discount). MenuSearch THC-low-band threshold "Low · under 15%" intentionally untouched (THC%, not discount). tsc clean.
// 7.405 — 🛡️ /api/products/by-ids GET — raw query-string length cap (4KB) BEFORE the .split()/.trim()/.test() pipeline runs over arbitrary input. Pre-fix a multi-MB ids parameter would burn CPU on the split + per-piece trim + per-piece regex test before the .slice(0, 16) ceiling could clip it. The 16-id ceiling + per-id alphanumeric regex was already enforced; this cap closes the cost-amplification flank on the public-anonymous read path. Sister mirror on glw v6.205. Sister to inv /api/admin/sparklines 16KB cap (v204.405) + the public-site input-cap arc.
// 7.385 — 🛡️ /api/track-install POST adds 10/min/IP rate limit + tighter source param length cap. Pre-fix the route was anonymous + un-rate-limited; each call writes an audit_log row (and sometimes a customers UPDATE) so a scripted spammer could inflate the install counter + balloon audit_log indefinitely. 10/min/IP is generous (real PWA install fires once on accept + once per cold standalone-launch). Source query param now caps raw at 256 chars BEFORE .trim()/.slice() runs (defense-in-depth on top of Next URL parsing). Sister mirror on glw v6.185. Sister to /api/quiz/capture (5/min/IP, v7.285) + inv /api/marketing/subscribe (3/min/IP, existing) defenses.
// 7.365 — 🔍 SEO redirect map round-2 expansion (Doug 2026-05-07: "same with seattle"). Mirror of glw v6.165's redirect-map work. **Routes added (~28):** wildcards `/shop/* /products/*` → `/menu`; missed categories `/prerolls /cartridges /topicals /tinctures /accessories` → `/menu`; `/strain/*` → `/find-your-strain`; legacy info-page paths `/contact-us /contact /location /locations /find-us /hours` → `/visit`; `/our-story /team /staff` → `/about`; `/privacy-policy /privacy /terms-of-service /terms-and-conditions /terms /tos` → `/about` (no real privacy/terms page; closest legal-disclosure surface is /about); WP archive paths `/author/* /blog/author/* /blog/category/* /blog/blog/* /tag/* /category/*` → `/blog`. All 308-permanent so existing inbound links + Google index entries resolve to a real page instead of 404. Sister: glw v6.165. tsc clean.
// 7.285 — 🛡️ `/api/quiz/capture` adds 5/min/IP rate limit. Each call inserts + fires Resend (per-email billing). 7-day dedupe per (email, source) prevents repeat-to-same-inbox; per-IP rate limit blocks the different-email loop. Sister mirror on glw v6.085. tsc clean.
// 7.205 — 🛡️ `/api/orders` adds 5/min/user rate limit. Each order-place call triggers INSERT + SMS confirm + email confirm + audit row — accidentally double-firing or a stuck retry loop fans out to staff (POS queue) + Twilio + Resend. Clerk auth gated; rate limits PER userId. Sister to glw v6.005 + inv `/api/customer/orders` (5/min/IP, existing). Pre-fix the public-site sister had only Vercel-edge body-size as defense. tsc clean.
// 7.105 — 🛡️ `/api/rewards/{request-code,verify-code}` add upfront length caps. Both routes call `normalizeToE164(body.phone)` which runs a regex strip — without the cap, a 10MB phone payload would burn CPU on the strip before the length check would reject. verify-code additionally calls `(body.code ?? "").trim()` before the `/^\\d{6}$/` regex check. New caps: phone 32 chars (E.164 max formatted ~17), code 16 (6 digits + slack). Same defense class as inv v190.645 (sister `/api/customer/auth/verify` input caps) + this session's input-cap arc. All Sea OTP-flow endpoints now bound input length before crypto + regex work. Single-file edit per route, ~6 LOC each. tsc clean.
// 7.025 — 🛡️ Public-site `/api/quiz/capture` + `/api/profile` add upfront length checks BEFORE `.trim()` / `.replace()` runs. Same defense class as the inv input-cap arc (v190.565 / v190.645 / v190.905 / v191.105 / v191.325 / v191.825). **What lands:** (1) quiz/capture: rawEmail rejects > 2× MAX_EMAIL_LEN raw input before .trim() runs; sanitize() rejects fields > 2× MAX_FIELD_LEN before .trim().slice(). (2) profile: cleanName + cleanPhone reject inputs > 200/64 chars before .trim() / regex .replace() runs over arbitrary input. Without this, a 10MB email or phone field would burn CPU on the trim/regex pass before the .slice() could cap downstream use. Sister mirror on glw v5.925. tsc clean.
// 6.945 — 🚨 Sea public-site /apply + /vendor-access + /careers were posting to WEN's inventoryapp (`inventoryapp-ivory.vercel.app`) instead of Sea's. Pre-fix every Seattle job applicant landed in Wen's hiring pipeline + Sea hiring pipeline never saw them; every Seattle vendor-access signup landed in Wen's vendor pipeline + Sea vendor team never saw them; the careers-page open-positions list pulled from Wen's DB so any Sea-side staff edits in `/admin/positions` weren't reflected on `seattlecannabis.co/careers`. Three hardcoded API_URL / POSITIONS_API constants (`apply/page.tsx:31-33`, `vendor-access/VendorAccessForm.tsx:6`, `careers/page.tsx:10`) all pointed at `inventoryapp-ivory.vercel.app` — a copy-paste leak from when the Sea public site was forked from Wen's (the v4.71 apply form shipped 2026-05-04, same day Sea got its own Neon DB per memory `project_seattle_neon_shared_with_wen`). Fix: replace with `seattle-cannabis-co.vercel.app` (Sea's canonical inv URL — matches `lib/closure-status.ts:14` which was already correct). Cross-store data-leak fixed; Sea applications + vendor signups now land in Sea's DB; Sea careers page reflects Sea's open-positions table. Mechanical 4 string replacements across 3 files. tsc clean.
// 6.885 — 🩺 /api/health now exposes `smsConfigured` boolean alongside `emailConfigured` — surfaces the OPEN TWILIO incident (INCIDENTS.md 2026-05-03 21:25 PT) on the public site's canonical health endpoint. Pre-fix the inventoryapp /api/health exposed smsConfigured but the public sites didn't, so monitoring scripts + Doug's curl-verify recipe couldn't see the SMS-config gap on scc / glw without separately checking inv. Mirrors lib/sms.ts `isSmsConfigured()` (already exported, used internally by sendSms() to no-op gracefully when env vars are missing). Boolean only — never exposes Twilio credentials. Once Doug pastes TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID + TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN + TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER into the 4 Vercel projects (~10 min, only blocker on the SpringBig 5/25 cutover), this field flips to `true` and the OPEN incident closes naturally. Sister: glw v5.845. Single import + single field per repo. tsc clean.
// 6.825 — 🛡️ `/api/orders` cart-item string-field length caps — defense-in-depth on the per-row INSERT to `online_order_items`. Pre-fix `productName` / `brand` / `category` / `strainType` / `productId` passed `typeof === "string"` checks but had no length bound. With `items.length > 50` already enforced, a malicious cart could send 50 × multi-MB strings to the DB INSERT row. Caps: productName 256, brand 128, category 64, strainType 32, productId 64 — all comfortable above natural cannabis product names (<100), brands (<40), categories (<16), strain-types (one of 3 words). In-place slice keeps the type check valid + doesn't reject — legitimate clients should never hit the cap. Sister mirror on glw v5.785. Single-file edit per repo, ~6 LOC. tsc clean.
// 6.745 — 🚨 /account/heroes page body had a stale 20% — canonical Heroes discount is 30%. The Heroes 20→30% sweep at v4.40 updated everything customer-facing, but the dedicated /account/heroes self-attest page was created later with copy-paste from the pre-sweep /account page, so the sweep missed it. Same drift class as v6.705 (the /account page subtitle): customer arriving via /account → "Heroes program" link would see "20% off" body text but every OTHER surface (visit / faq / homepage / OG / heroes/[cohort] / rewards/redeem) advertises 30%. Single-line "20% off" → "30% off". Sister: glw v5.665. tsc clean.
// 6.705 — 🚨 /account Heroes-program subtitle had a stale 20% — canonical Heroes discount is 30% across both stores (matches /heroes, /faq, /llms.txt, all other surfaces). Pre-fix the Account page was telling Heroes-eligible customers they'd save 20% — they'd arrive at the counter expecting 20%, customer would be confused. Sister: glw v5.625.
