// 6.625 — 🐛 /llms-full.txt no-stacking copy fix — Q&A about deals/loyalty was saying "The 15% off first online order applies on top of any active deal" which directly contradicts Doug's no-stacking policy (memory `feedback_no_stacking_ever`). Replaced with "Discounts don't combine — best discount applies. Loyalty points still earn on every visit regardless of which discount is in play." Sister: glw v5.465.
// 6.585 — /accessibility WEB_A11Y_NOTES expanded — adds 2 new claims documenting the v5.875 (focus indicator / WCAG 2.4.7) + v6.225 (loading-state announcements / WCAG 4.1.3) ADA ships. ADA Title III defensive copy. Sister: glw v5.385.
// 6.385 — 🛡️ `/api/push/unsubscribe` adds 1024-char endpoint length cap — symmetric with `/api/push/subscribe`'s existing cap. Defense-in-depth: without the cap, a malicious caller could send a multi-MB endpoint string that bogs down the DELETE query's index probe + bloats Vercel response logs. Subscribe already capped at 1024 (length 1024 / p256dh 256 / auth 64 — the natural sizes for a Web Push API endpoint); unsubscribe inherited none of those checks because the route was a thinner DELETE-by-endpoint with no upsert validation. Sister mirror on glw v5.265. Single-file edit, ~5 LOC. tsc clean.
// 6.305 — 🛡️ `/api/push/send` Bearer-token compare uses `crypto.timingSafeEqual` instead of `===`. Sister of glw v5.185 + auth-class hardening continuation from v6.025 / v6.105. Pre-fix `authz !== expected` short-circuits on first differing byte — measurable timing side-channel proportional to how many leading characters of `PUSH_SEND_TOKEN` an attacker has correctly guessed. Practical risk small (PUSH_SEND_TOKEN is admin-curated + rotates if compromised + the worst-case impact of a stolen token is sending unauthorized push notifications to subscribed customers, not customer-data leakage), but the rest of the codebase already uses timing-safe compare for all secret-equality checks (lib/rewards-session.ts, /api/rewards/verify-code at v6.105). Length-mismatch short-circuits before timingSafeEqual (which throws on differing buffer lengths and length isn't a secret). Single-file edit. tsc clean.
// 6.225 — ADA accessibility round 3 — root loading.tsx Suspense fallback announces to screen readers (WCAG 4.1.3 Status Messages). Pre-fix the customer-side spinner had no role=status / aria-live / aria-busy — users with screen readers heard NOTHING during loading. Adds the three ARIA attributes + aria-hidden on the decorative spinner div so screen readers announce just the visible "Loading…" text once. Sister: glw v5.065 + inv v186.765.
// 6.105 — 🛡️ `/api/rewards/verify-code` OTP-hash compare uses `crypto.timingSafeEqual` instead of `===`. Practical risk in this specific endpoint was ~zero (MAX_ATTEMPTS=5 + 10-min TTL caps probes far below what's needed to extract bytes via timing, network jitter dwarfs per-byte signal), but `===` short-circuits on first differing byte and timing-safe compare is the right pattern for any hash/HMAC comparison — defense-in-depth + matches the inventoryapp's own `verifyOtp` (lib/auth.ts:483) which already uses `constantTimeEqual`. Single-line addition (`timingSafeEqual` from `node:crypto`) + ~5-line replacement of the compare expression: convert both hashes to Buffers via `Buffer.from(..., "hex")`, length-check, then `timingSafeEqual`. Auth-class pattern hardening — same defense class as v6.025 OTP-leak gate. tsc clean.
// 6.025 — 🛡️ `/api/rewards/request-code` belt-and-suspenders against OTP-code leak if Twilio env vars drift on production. The endpoint returns `{ demoCode: code }` when `isSmsConfigured()` is false so devs can complete the verify flow without an external SMS during preview/dev. The original comment said "Production builds always have Twilio configured; this leak path is preview-only." — but if env vars ever became misconfigured in prod (partial restore from another env, accidental unset of TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID, drift between Wen and Sea Vercel projects), the leak would actually fire — anyone could request an OTP for any phone number and read the code in the response, bypassing the SMS gate entirely. Defense: gate the demoCode branch on `process.env.VERCEL_ENV === "production"` — if PROD AND SMS unconfigured, log a critical-error console line + return generic HTTP 500 to the client. If preview/dev AND SMS unconfigured, return demoCode as before (dev convenience preserved). Trade: prod misconfig surfaces as a 500 to the customer instead of silent OTP-leak — failing closed is the right posture for an auth-flow endpoint. Single-file edit, ~10 LOC added. tsc clean.
// 5.945 — `/heroes` FAQ answers tightened — 2 small content ports from glw heroes/page.tsx that close customer-question gaps. (1) "What if my ID is expired?" answer adds "— those are permanent records" tail clarifying WHY DD-214 / VA card / VHIC stay valid as eligibility proof even when other IDs expire (eligibility-proof IDs are permanent records, vs current-credential IDs that need to stay current). (2) "Why two IDs?" answer adds "Both are needed." final sentence so the customer leaves the section with the explicit two-ID requirement, not a maybe. Both edits live in the FAQS const which feeds both the visible accordion AND the FAQPage JSON-LD payload — same content lifts to AI engines + Google rich results. Did NOT port glw's "Industry-discount cohorts have a different rule (90-day re-verify) but Heroes is open-ended" tail because Sea doesn't have an Industry-discount cohort yet (verified — no `industry-discount` references in app/), and mentioning a non-existent cohort would confuse Sea customers. Single-file edit, 2 single-string changes. tsc clean.
// 5.875 — ADA accessibility round 2 — global :focus-visible safety-net ring (WCAG 2.4.7). Sister of glw v5.025. Indigo-600 ring matches Sea brand. Most components have explicit Tailwind focus-visible:ring-... classes, but legacy buttons inherited focus:outline-none from a parent without painting their own — keyboard users had no visible focus indicator. Single global rule paints a 2px ring on any :focus-visible element. Mouse clicks don't flicker (:focus-visible only matches keyboard focus). Components already painting a custom ring can opt out via no-default-focus class.
// 5.825 — ADA accessibility round 1 — globals.css honors prefers-reduced-motion: reduce. Sister of glw v4.985. Pre-fix ~20 customer-facing sites used animate-pulse/spin/bounce without a motion-reduce: Tailwind variant — users with vestibular conditions / migraine triggers / motion sensitivity saw all animations regardless of OS pref (WCAG 2.3.3 / SC-2.3.3). Blanket CSS override slows ALL animations + transitions to near-static (0.01ms) when the OS pref is set + explicit animation: none on common Tailwind motion classes. Single CSS edit covers ~20 sites without per-component refactors. Doug 2026-05-07 ADA pass.
// 5.735 — **Homepage FAQPage JSON-LD + accordion section — closes the GEO/AI-engine sister gap with Wen.** v5.705 shipped HowTo schema for the 3-step pickup flow but explicitly deferred the FAQ section ("FAQs are Sea-specific copy, ~120 LOC"). This is that ship. **What lands:** 8-question FAQPage block above the bottom CTA band, each rendered as an `<details>` accordion AND emitted as `@type: Question` / `@type: Answer` in a `<script type="application/ld+json">` payload — so AI Overviews / ChatGPT / Perplexity can lift answers verbatim, and Google SERP can render the rich-result expander. Sea-specific copy throughout: Rainier Valley framing on Q1 (location), uniform 8 AM–11 PM hours on Q2 (no Fri/Sat-extended footnote like Wen), Seattle local sales tax (~10.25%) on Q8 (vs Wenatchee's ~8.8%), 15% online-discount mention on Q5 (Sea's commerce hook). Mirrors Wen's structure (`app/page.tsx` `FaqSection` at v4.665+); same JSON-LD shape so trust signals lift symmetrically across both stores in AI engines. tsc clean. 1 file edit (~95 LOC added).
// 5.725 — **frequencyPref selector ported from glw v4.435 — closes a missed-mirror gap on Sea.** Wen has had the 3-button Update-Frequency tier ('Just essentials' ≤2/mo · 'Standard' ≤4/mo · 'More updates' ≤8/mo) on `/account/profile` since v4.435, alongside the email-opt-in toggle that Sea already mirrored at v5.225/v5.255. The DB column (`portal_users.frequency_pref`) shipped via inventoryapp migration 0213 to BOTH stores' Neons — but the Sea public-site code never read or wrote it. Net effect: Sea customers had no way to dial marketing-frequency up or down; downstream `lib/marketing-touches.ts` FREQUENCY_CAPS used the default 4/mo for everyone. **Ships:** (1) `lib/portal.ts` PortalUser type adds `frequencyPref: "low" \| "standard" \| "high"`; existing SELECT + INSERT RETURNING + UPDATE clauses include `frequency_pref`; mapPortalUser reads with "standard" fallback. (2) `app/api/profile/route.ts` POST handler accepts `frequencyPref`, validates against the enum allowlist before passing to updatePortalUser. (3) `app/account/profile/ProfileForm.tsx` adds the 3-button grid (indigo theme matching Sea palette) between Email Notifications and No Substitutions. Sister to glw v4.435 — same pattern, Sea-styled. tsc clean. 3 file edits.
// 5.715 — `/menu` + `MenuFallback` close-time copy now reads today's hours via new `todayCloseLabel()` helper instead of `STORE.hours[0]?.close`. Sea is uniform 11 PM every day today so this is defensive (no visible current drift), but the helper prevents the same bug class that hit Wen on Friday/Saturday when its hours diverge from Monday's row — `STORE.hours[0]?.close` always returns the Monday entry. Sister to greenlife-web v4.835 (which had the visible drift). tsc clean.
// 5.705 — Homepage HowTo JSON-LD — closes SEO sister gap with Wen. Wen homepage has had a HowTo schema block (v4.665ish) for the 3-step pickup flow + a FAQPage schema (v3.x); SCC homepage had visible 3-step content but ZERO JSON-LD — meaning AI Overviews + ChatGPT couldn't cite or lift the steps verbatim, and Google's rich-result rendering had nothing to work with. Added the HowTo schema (mirrors Wen v4.665 with Sea-specific copy: 15% online discount, ${STORE.name}, /order route). Pre-fix SCC was the visible-content-but-no-schema state — content lift to AI engines = 0%. FaqSection mirror is a separate larger ship (FAQs are Sea-specific copy, ~120 LOC). tsc clean.
// 5.665 — /treasure-chest added to sitemap. Surface shipped v5.045 + linked from /menu strip + homepage pill, but `app/sitemap.ts` was never updated — Google never crawl-discovered the clearance lane. Pre-fix only customers who navigated the homepage pill OR /menu strip ever saw it. Adding with daily changeFrequency (inventory turns) + 0.7 priority. Sister: glw v4.825. tsc clean.
// 5.625 — /menu page now respects PWA install cookie for app-only deals — closes the install-incentive gap on the most-visited customer page. Pre-fix /menu called getActiveDeals() without args, so installed visitors saw the same `app_only=false` subset as browser-only — losing the install incentive on the deals strip. Fix: read `scc_pwa_installed` cookie, pass `includeAppOnly`. 4-surface coverage complete: /deals list (v5.345), /deals/[id] (v5.605), homepage strip (v5.525), /menu strip (this). Sister: glw v4.745. tsc clean.
// 5.605 — /deals/[id] deep page now gates app-only deals on PWA install — closes the SMS-share leak that bypassed the install incentive. Pre-fix: getDealById() SQL didn't query the app_only column; hardcoded appOnly: false with comment "filter happens upstream in getActiveDeals." But the deep page calls getDealById DIRECTLY — so a customer sharing /deals/<app-only-id> via SMS, the recipient (not installed) could view the full discount + landing page, bypassing the install gate that's the whole point. Fix: (1) getDealById() SELECTs COALESCE(app_only, FALSE) + returns it. (2) /deals/[id]/page.tsx reads the scc_pwa_installed cookie post-fetch — if appOnly && !isInstalled, calls notFound() (same shape as stale share link). (3) generateMetadata does the same gate so the unfurl preview doesn't leak the discount in the OG card before install. Net effect: app-only deals opaque to non-installed visitors regardless of access path — list + deep-page + OG preview all gated. tsc clean.
// 5.545 — **`cross_store_promo` slot mounted on homepage between brands and CTA band.** Mirror of glw v4.625. Slot was admin-pickable but had no public mount. tsc clean.
// 5.525 — **Homepage Today's-deals strip respects the app-install cookie.** Mirror of glw v4.575. v5.345 added the cookie + filter on /deals; homepage was unconditionally fetching all active deals. Now reads `scc_pwa_installed` cookie + passes `includeAppOnly` to getActiveDeals. tsc clean.
// 5.505 — **`/api/rewards/verify-code` retroactively attributes PWA installs at OTP sign-in.** Sister fix to v5.385 — closes the install-before-signin attribution gap on the migration funnel. **Problem:** /api/track-install only sets `customers.scc_app_installed_at` when a Clerk session is active. The typical flow is (a) install PWA anonymously → (b) open /rewards → (c) sign in via OTP, so step (a)'s install never gets attributed to the customer at all. The migration-funnel "Installed new SCC app" tile on inventoryapp /admin/marketing was undercounting by exactly the install-before-signin cohort (= the entire dominant flow). **Fix:** verify-code now reads the `scc_pwa_installed=1` cookie (set by /api/track-install on first standalone-mode hit) and, when present, back-fills `customers.scc_app_installed_at` for the matched phone alongside the existing `rewards_signed_in_at` stamp. Both writes are COALESCE-guarded (idempotent — first install + first sign-in both stick), both run inside the existing `after()` block (no login-latency cost). Privacy posture unchanged: silent UPDATE on no-match preserves the no-customer-existence-reveal property. **Net effect:** the funnel now reflects reality — every customer who installed and signed in shows in both the installed AND signed-in tiles regardless of whether they were Clerk-authed at install time. tsc clean. 1 file +14 LOC.
// 5.465 — **STORE_TZ SSoT arc — Sea sister to greenlife-web v4.535. ~14 inline `"America/Los_Angeles"` literals across 12 consumers migrated to import the canonical constant from `@/lib/store`.** Closes the same drift-class arc inventoryapp v167.665 closed. Ships: (1) `lib/store.ts` exports `STORE_TZ`; the existing internal `const TZ` aliases it (no behavior change). (2) Inline literals migrated in: `app/page.tsx`, `app/order/confirmation/[id]/page.tsx`, `app/rewards/history/page.tsx`, `app/about/page.tsx`, `app/visit/page.tsx`, `app/api/orders/route.ts`, `app/account/page.tsx`, `app/account/orders/page.tsx`, `components/AnnouncementBar.tsx`, `components/MobileStickyCta.tsx`, `lib/deal-countdown.ts`. tsc clean.
// 5.405 — **3 new VendorAdSlot mounts on scc — `menu_top`, `deals_page_top`, `treasure_chest_top`.** Mirror of glw v4.555. Pairs with inv v180.345 enum extension. Doug 2026-05-07: more display-ad slots for vendor + cross-store reciprocal advertising (no money exchange). Each mount is a 1-line `<VendorAdSlot slot="..." />` near the top of the page; component returns null when no active ads. Slots become curatable on /admin/marketing/vendor-ads once inv v180.345 deploys. tsc clean. 3 files.
// 5.385 — **`/api/rewards/verify-code` stamps `customers.rewards_signed_in_at` after successful OTP login.** Closes the second leg of the SpringBig→SCC migration funnel (inventoryapp v179.865 admin tile already shipped reading this column). Pairs with v179.565's migration 0215 schema. **Behavior:** `COALESCE(rewards_signed_in_at, NOW())` so the timestamp captures the FIRST sign-in only — subsequent logins don't bump it (preserves the migration-funnel "moment of first activation" signal). Wired via Next 16 `after()` so the UPDATE runs post-response — login latency unchanged + UPDATE failure can't break sign-in. Privacy posture intact: we already issue the cookie purely on OTP match without confirming customer existence, and the UPDATE is silent (zero rows affected when no customer with this phone) — server learns nothing an attacker probing this endpoint couldn't already learn. **Funnel chain now wired end-to-end:** SpringBig data import flips `springbig_app_installed=TRUE` → /api/track-install sets `scc_app_installed_at` on PWA install → /api/rewards/verify-code sets `rewards_signed_in_at` on first /rewards login → inventoryapp /admin/marketing tile renders cohort/installed/signed-in counts. tsc clean. 1 file +20 LOC.
// 5.345 — **App-only deals filter — public /deals hides `app_only=true` deals from non-PWA customers.** Closes the loop on Doug 2026-05-07: "special deals through the app." **Ships:** (1) `getActiveDeals({ includeAppOnly })` — new opt arg; defaults FALSE so non-installed customers see only public deals. SQL gains `AND (${includeAppOnly} = TRUE OR COALESCE(app_only, FALSE) = FALSE)` so the filter is one round-trip. COALESCE handles pre-migration databases where the column hasn't been added yet (= every deal app_only=false). (2) `/api/track-install` POST now sets a `scc_pwa_installed=1` cookie (1-year maxAge, sameSite=lax) on every call. Cookie value is just a presence marker; the standalone-launch path refreshes it on every PWA open. (3) `/deals` server component reads the cookie via Next 16 `cookies()` and passes `includeAppOnly={isInstalled}` to the fetcher. (4) `ActiveDeal` type gains `appOnly: boolean` field (Sea + Wen mirror — bumps both type signatures + 2 consumers updated). **End-to-end:** customer installs PWA → /api/track-install drops cookie → next /deals visit shows app_only deals. Browser-only visitors see the InstallAppBanner + no app_only deals (intended — install incentive). Pairs with inv v179.785 schema + v179.945 admin checkbox. tsc clean. 3 files.
// 5.305 — **NEW `/api/track-install` endpoint + InstallAppBanner attribution wiring — \"how many downloads our new app has.\"** Doug 2026-05-07: \"lets also keep track of how many downloads our new app has.\" **Ships:** (1) `app/api/track-install/route.ts` — POST records an install with optional `?source` (e.g. springbig_migration / android_accepted / ios_sheet_opened / standalone_launch / organic). Writes audit_log row + (when Clerk session present) sets `customers.scc_app_installed_at` via portal_user → customer phone/email match. (2) GET returns aggregate counters: `total`, `last7d`, `attributedCustomers`. Public — Doug can curl `seattlecannabis.co/api/track-install` anytime, no admin gate. (3) `InstallAppBanner` `recordInstall(source)` fires fire-and-forget after Android `installEvent.prompt()` accept + iOS share-sheet open. (4) Standalone-mode useEffect path POSTs `?source=standalone_launch` ONCE per browser session via sessionStorage sentinel — captures iOS installs where appinstalled doesn't fire + all prior installs without attribution. **Counter math:** `total` = all installs ever (per launch + per accept). `attributedCustomers` = DISTINCT entity_id COUNT — = unique customers who installed. Migration funnel: source breakdown shows attribution per channel. Pairs with inventoryapp v179.565 schema migration (customers.scc_app_installed_at column). tsc clean.
// 5.265 — **InstallAppBanner copy refresh — leads with "App-only deals."** Doug 2026-05-07: "special deals through the app (we can add this on the ad on our page to try to advertise our own app)." Old copy: "Order faster, see your rewards, get drop notifications." New: "App-only deals · your rewards · drop notifications · faster ordering." App-only deals leads since it's the strongest install incentive — pairs with future app-only deal mechanic (`deals.app_only` flag + filter on /deals visible only when standalone-mode === true). Single-line copy fix.
// 5.245 — **NEW InstallAppBanner mirrored from greenlife-web v4.435 — Sea PWA install nudge for the SpringBig-customer migration funnel.** Doug 2026-05-07: "get an app launched for seattle too maybe we can get those 1000 customers over." The /rewards PWA was already shipped (dashboard / redeem / history with OTP sign-in, mobile bottom-nav from v5.105) — what was missing was the install nudge to drive existing customers from the browser to the home screen. **Ships:** (1) `components/InstallAppBanner.tsx` mirrored from glw with Sea branding (indigo-700 instead of green-700, "Seattle Cannabis" copy, separate localStorage key `scc-install-banner-dismissed-at` with 30d cool-down). (2) Mounted in `app/layout.tsx` so it renders on every customer-facing page on mobile. **Behavior:** mobile-only render (display:none above 900px), hidden when running standalone (already installed) or after dismiss, Android captures `beforeinstallprompt` event + fires on tap, iOS Safari shows step-by-step Share→Add-to-Home-Screen sheet. **Migration funnel context:** when SpringBig data import lands, customers with `springbigAppInstalled=true` flag will get differentiated SMS messaging (Doug 2026-05-07 ask). For now: banner on every page nudges install; OTP sign-in matches existing rewards records by phone/email; install rate measurable via /api/health 'installed via PWA' surface (separate ship). tsc clean. 2 files.
