// 4.395 — Brand-name cleanup at the lib boundary. Mirror of greenlife-web v3.555. Companion to v4.365 logo-filter. Even with the carousel filter, vendor names like "Alpha Crux, llc" and "Northwest Cannabis Solutions LLC" still leak into customer-visible surfaces (`/brands/[slug]` page H1, brand-deal callouts, future brand-attribution text). New `lib/clean-brand-name.ts` exports `cleanBrandName(raw)` which strips trailing legal-entity suffixes (`, LLC` / ` LLC` / ` Inc` / ` Corp` / ` Co` / ` Ltd` / ` PLLC` and dotted variants) only when anchored to end-of-string. Conservative: doesn't touch numeric prefixes, doesn't touch ` - <text>` patterns, doesn't strip mid-string LLC. Applied at `lib/db.ts` `getActiveBrands()` + `getBrandBySlug()` row mappings — single point of truth. Slug derivation still uses canonical `v.name` so URLs are stable. tsc clean.
// 4.365 — Top Brands carousel filters to logo'd brands. Pre-fix the homepage "Washington's finest producers / Top Brands" section sliced the first 10 alphabetical brands from `getActiveBrands()`, surfacing license-shaped vendor records ("1555 Industrial L...", "AG GROW - 4125...", "Alpha Crux, llc") rendered with single-letter initial placeholders — visually a wall of "A"/"B" cards with zero actual logos, the opposite of the section heading's promise. Post-fix: filter `b.logoUrl != null && b.logoUrl.trim().length > 0` BEFORE the .slice(0, 10) so only brands with real uploaded logos are eligible. Existing `featuredBrands.length > 0` guard below already hides the whole section when the filter returns empty (no awkward 1-card-row state). Initials fallback in the JSX stays as defense-in-depth for the rare case a brand's logoUrl returns 404 at render. Mirror on greenlife-web v3.485. Single-file ship. tsc clean.
// 4.355 — Order-status mapping fix. Mirror of greenlife-web v3.475. Inventoryapp's POS PATCH writes `in_progress` and `fulfilled` to `online_orders.status` (per inventoryapp's pos/online-orders/[id]/route.ts), but this app's `OnlineOrder["status"]` type and UI label maps use `preparing` and `picked_up`. Pre-fix: lib/portal.ts read paths cast raw DB string to the type without value transformation, so `STATUS_LABEL[order.status]` resolved to `undefined` — customer's `/account/orders` row + `/order/confirmation/[id]` timeline rendered blank when a budtender hit Start Order or marked picked up. Post-fix: new `normalizeOrderStatus()` helper maps `in_progress` → `preparing`, `fulfilled` → `picked_up`, passes other valid statuses through, falls back to `pending` for unknown. Applied in both `getOrder()` and `getOrders()` return mappings. tsc clean.
